<br>
Total: 40 + 3 Magi   </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">Zannah is the perfect non-setup lead Magi for Naroom. So often players won&#39;t have the answer in their opening hand. Basically Zannah exists not to go all out but to frustrate the opponent&#39;s early efforts, and DRAW YAKI CARDS! She can do so without letting up her attack, unlike Wence or Evu who have trouble being offensive enough to contain the opposition. Once Yaki is out the fun begins; the Forest Hyren-Weebo combo turns the game around almost all the time and it will take TWO Shockwaves to nuetralize it. Giving Yaki 2 big creatures is a warrant for the head of your opponent, hahaha! Don&#39;t overextend though, keep some cards for Tryn, who is still the Queen of Naroom!<br>
Your relics are the source of your growth, don&#39;t use them carelessly, as a Beam of Light could screw you over if you don&#39;t time it right. Lockdown Weave, Sorreah&#39;s Effect, Charm, or basically WHATEVER THE OBVIOUS THREAT IS. Save your Shockwaves for true dangers too; you should be able to handle 6-7 energy creatures in combat pretty often. Essence of Naroom works in about half the decks I face (a little more actually) but just about every metagame has alot of Naroom and Weave. 2 dead cards in the deck against other decks is WAY worth the turnaround you get for using these when you can. </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000"> </Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">DeckTech <BR> For the Players, By the Players  <BR>www.decktech.net </FONT></TD></TR></table> 
